</span></span><span class="mspace mtight" style="margin-right: 0.1952em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mop">lo<span style="margin-right: 0.0139em;">g</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mop">lo<span style="margin-right: 0.0139em;">g</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span><span class="mclose delimcenter" style="top: 0em;"><span class="delimsizing size1">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li><li>None of these</li></ol><p></p><i style="font-size:1em;">Question Type : <b>Multiple Choice</b>;Marks for correct answer <font color="green"><b>1</b></font>; Negative Marks <font color="red"><b> 0.2500</b></font></i><hr style="border-top-style: inset; border-top-width: 1px; color: rgb(204, 204, 204);"><p></p><p style="padding-left:5px"></p><table><tbody><tr><td>Q. 20) </td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p><span style="display: none;" id="cke_bm_93S">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p><p>Consider these two traversals of the tree shown:</p><p><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>1.&nbsp;boa,&nbsp;copperhead,&nbsp;python,&nbsp;viper,&nbsp;taipan,&nbsp;mamba</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{1. boa, copperhead, python, viper, taipan, mamba}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">1.&nbsp;boa,&nbsp;copperhead,&nbsp;python,&nbsp;viper,&nbsp;taipan,&nbsp;mamba</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>2.&nbsp;mamba,&nbsp;copperhead,&nbsp;boa,&nbsp;taipan,&nbsp;python,&nbsp;viper</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{2. mamba, copperhead, boa, taipan, python, viper}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">2.&nbsp;mamba,&nbsp;copperhead,&nbsp;boa,&nbsp;taipan,&nbsp;python,&nbsp;viper</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p>Which one statement below is true about these traversals?</p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>1 is postorder, 2 is preorder</li><li>1 is postorder, and 2 is not preorder</li><li>1 is not postorder, and 2 is preorder</li><li>1 is not postorder, and 2 is not preorder</li></ol><p></p><i style="font-size:1em;">Question Type : <b>Multiple Choice</b>;Marks for correct answer <font color="green"><b>1</b></font>; Negative Marks <font color="red"><b> 0.2500</b></font></i><hr style="border-top-style: inset; border-top-width: 1px; color: rgb(204, 204, 204);"><p></p><p style="padding-left:5px"></p><table><tbody><tr><td>Q. 21) </td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p>For a given predicate <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathrm{P}(\mathrm{x})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathrm">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>, you might believe that the statements <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∀</mi><mi>x</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\forall x \mathrm{P}(\mathrm{x})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∀</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mord mathrm">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span> or <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∃</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\exists \mathrm{xP}(\mathrm{x})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∃</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">xP</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span> are either true or false.<br><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∃</mi><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">¬</mi><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\exists x(\neg P(x))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∃</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">¬</span><span style="margin-right: 0.1389em;" class="mord mathnormal">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span></span></span> is false if and only if</p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∃</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\exists \mathrm{x}(\mathrm{P}(\mathrm{x}))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∃</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span></span></span> is true.</li><li><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∀</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\forall \mathrm{x}(\mathrm{P}(\mathrm{x}))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∀</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span></span></span> is true.</li><li><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∀</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">¬</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\forall \mathrm{x}(\neg \mathrm{P}(\mathrm{x}))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∀</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">¬</span><span class="mord mathrm">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathrm">x</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span></span></span> is true.</li><li><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∀</mi><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">¬</mi><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\forall x(\neg P(x))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∀</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">¬</span><span style="margin-right: 0.1389em;" class="mord mathnormal">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span></span></span> is false.</li></ol><p></p><i style="font-size:1em;">Question Type : <b>Multiple Choice</b>;Marks for correct answer <font color="green"><b>1</b></font>; Negative Marks <font color="red"><b> 0.2500</b></font></i><hr style="border-top-style: inset; border-top-width: 1px; color: rgb(204, 204, 204);"><p></p><p style="padding-left:5px"></p><table><tbody><tr><td>Q. 22) </td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p>We have relations <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">R(a, b)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span style="margin-right: 0.0077em;" class="mord mathnormal">R</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">a</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">b</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span> and <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>c</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">S(a, c)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span style="margin-right: 0.0576em;" class="mord mathnormal">S</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">a</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">c</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>.<br>Suppose the following SQL statement holds:</p><pre data-pbcklang="sql" data-pbcktabsize="4" class="prettyprint linenums lang-sql">NOT EXISTS (SELECT * FROM R, S WHERE R.a = S.a AND R.b&lt;&gt;S.c)</pre><p><br>Which of the following combinations of tuples are prohibited from existing at the same time?</p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator="true">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">(1,1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span> in <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span style="margin-right: 0.0077em;" class="mord mathnormal">R</span></span></span></span></span> and <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator="true">,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">(2,2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span