 protocol used by a router or destination host to communicate with the 
source, typically to report errors in IP datagram processing.</p><ol start="1" style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>ARP</li><li>ICMP</li><li>TCP</li><li>DNS</li></ol><p></p><i style="font-size:1em;">Question Type : <b>Multiple Choice</b>;Marks for correct answer <font color="green"><b>1</b></font>; Negative Marks <font color="red"><b> 0.2500</b></font></i><hr style="border-top-style: inset; border-top-width: 1px; color: rgb(204, 204, 204);"><p></p><p style="padding-left:5px"></p><table><tbody><tr><td>Q. 24) </td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p>Consider the following predicates.</p><ul><li><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Rabbit</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Rabbit}(x) = x</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Rabbit</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span></span></span></span></span> is a rabbit.</li><li><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Cute</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Cute}(x) = x</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Cute</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span></span></span></span></span> is cute.</li></ul><p>Consider the following statement <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>E</mtext><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{E},</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">E</span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span></span></span></span></span> where the domain of every variable is set of all animals in a jungle <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>J</mtext><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{J}.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">J</span></span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span><br><span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>E</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">∀</mi><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mtext>Rabbit</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>∧</mo><mtext>Cute</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{E} = \forall x ( \text{Rabbit}(x) \wedge \text{Cute}(x) )</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">E</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">∀</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Rabbit</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">∧</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Cute</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span></span></span></p><p>If statement <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>E</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{E}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">E</span></span></span></span></span></span> is true, then which of the following is false?</p><ol start="1" style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>There is no animal other than rabbits in the jungle <span><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>J<